# Project Onboarding — Welcome to the DDD Template

## Overview

This skill is the **entry point** for someone new to this repository. The goal is
to give them a clear mental model in under 10 minutes and point them to the right
deeper resources when they want to learn more.

Use a friendly, concise tone. Do not dump all knowledge at once — answer what was
asked, then offer the next step.

## What This Template Is

A production-ready **DDD + Hexagonal Architecture** template for TypeScript / Node.js
services. Battle-tested building blocks (transactional Unit of Work, automatic
aggregate tracking, event store, multi-tenancy, SSE, observability) wired together
with a complete `User` reference module so a new dev can read one feature
end-to-end and ship their own.

**Stack:** TypeScript 5.9 (strict) · Node 24+ · `node:test` · ESM · SWC on-the-fly
(no build step) · MikroORM 7 + SQLite (default, swappable to Postgres) · GraphQL +
REST out of the box.

## The 5-Minute Tour

When asked for a tour, walk the user through these in order:

1. **`README.md`** — overview, quickstart, full feature matrix
2. **`CLAUDE.md`** — concise reference for AI tools and humans (key base classes, conventions, TS constraints)
3. **`AGENTS.md`** — generic AI tooling pointer (for Cursor, Copilot, Codex, Aider, Cline, Continue)
4. **`docs/architecture.md`** — full request flow with Mermaid diagram
5. **`docs/adding-a-bounded-context.md`** — step-by-step walkthrough with copy-paste snippets
6. **`docs/adrs/`** — Architecture Decision Records (the "why" behind every major choice)

## The 3-Minute Code Tour

Read these files in order and the architecture clicks:

1. `src/shared/domain/aggregates/AggregateRoot.ts` — the base class with auto-tracking
2. `src/shared/application/ApplicationService.ts` — the orchestrator (`begin → execute → drain → dispatch → publish → saveAll → commit → broadcast`)
3. `src/modules/user/domain/User.ts` — a real aggregate (create, addAddress, removeAddress)
4. `src/modules/user/application/usecase/CreateUserUseCase.ts` — a real use case (returns `User` directly, never calls `.save()`)
5. `src/modules/user/infrastructure/persistence/mikro-orm/UserAggregatePersister.ts` — how persistence is wired generically
6. `src/main.ts` — composition root (factories + module registration)

